1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
AMDA — Verify Before You Pay

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Track 1 scores accuracy first, then ranks by tokens spent.
Local tokens are free.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:20,000
So the scarce resource isn't capability —
it's confidence in a free answer.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:30,000
AMDA verifies before it escalates: code is executed,
math is re-derived, logic is solved independently.

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Only a genuine verification failure calls a paid
remote model — throttled and capped.

6
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Live run: the exact image pushed to GHCR,
under the real 2 vCPU / 4GB grading constraint.

7
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:56,000
5 of 8 tasks resolved locally — zero token cost.

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Only 3 tasks escalated — 33 output tokens, total.

9
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:15,000
228-task internal benchmark. Math: 28/28 once verified.
Logic: 92% solver accuracy.

10
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:25,000
We read real competitor code. No one else
re-derives answers before spending a paid token.

11
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Verify locally. Escalate surgically.
Spend only where correctness demands it.

12
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:38,000
AMDA — built for AMD Developer Hackathon Act II, Track 1.
